76561198022809025,Recommended,250620,10281972,"Posted: 29 May, 2014",all,Jessica Jesibiel,"The game provides excellent graphics, traversing through the realm of a 2 year olds reality will change your point of view of the world completely, nothing seems as it should.The game had only one flaw, it was very short which unfortunantly seems unfair for such a high price, nevertheless i am impressed of the gameplay.I dont regret buying and playing the game, it really changed my point of view, of how something innocent can in reality be far worse than you could imagine....and what is it?...well...play and see for yourself...."
,Recommended,250620,10284049,"Posted: 30 May, 2014",all,walkmandosch,"Once again, Krillbite studio has brought us on a thought provoking adventure. Their first being The Plan, which was a 'preview' of their first shot at developing with the Unity engine... and quite frankly changed my view of what defines a good game in a matter of 2 minutes time.It seems that this small group of developers has a knack of thinking outside of the box. Again using the Unity engine, Among the Sleep puts you in the unique position of viewing the world through the eyes of a two year old. Never before has a lovable protagonist been so helpless. Using this gameplay method in a horror game is a stroke of genious, since you have no way of defending yourself against unknown evils. It really adds to the feeling of helplessness. Periodic jumpscares plus extraordinary psychologically tense background noise creates an unnerving edge-of-your seat venture.This game is not without its flaws. Glitches abound, and the the monotone surroundings feel clausterphobic at times. I also found that for the price, it was surprisingly short.This game could use some depth and length, but all in all, it was a very unique experience that I would recommend for gamers who enjoy something new. 8/10."
