,Recommended,250620,16582171,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,Roopoo,"I remember my first teddy bear when I was a little girl. His name was Rufus. He was actually my best friend for a long time until I was able to imagine friends without the need of a physical face.He still huddles among the boots of my closet, negotiating with all the sock-monsters in there.For many children, the security of a soft, cuddly friend can really make or break their day, and there is something incredibly endearing in being able to experience this through the eyes of a toddler, as an adult.The knowledge that such simple things seem so terrifying at such a young age, makes complete sense when you understand that a child's mind is bursting with unbridled creativity.- I recommend you play with headphones for full immersion.As a whole, I loved this game.The storyline was surprisingly refreshing - it's odd how stereotypical visions have a tendency to creep up on your subconscious, grab you by the heels and shout 'Gotcha!' even when you think you have them equalled.- Short and sweet. My only complaint to be that it could have been a little longer, though there is an epilogue that I also recommend playing through.SO many cuddles for Teddy.If you have a few hours to spare, I suggest trying out Among the Sleep."
