,Recommended,250620,18300745,"Posted: 2 October, 2015",all,Vash(88),"Awesome game!  The ""story,"" foreshadowing, unique gameplay, atmosphere and clever level design are all presented well in this game.  The only downside is the length, even though it feels appropriate given the lack of gameplay mechanics the  devs had to work with.The cleverness to the scare tactics was genius.  Just like when I was a kid, it was the unknown that scared me the most.  So much of this game works on the player's imagination instead of cheap jump-scares.  In a lot of horror games, it is common to start predicting the scary section which can often soften the blow.  Not in this game.  The ambiance is done  well enough that the anticipation of a predictable scare actually makes it worse.  Kind of like being in a dream and knowing that it's going bad.They did such a good job with the sound effects.  The bumps, creaks, groans, smashes, screams and cries all drive the unsettled nerves home.The devs also did an excellent job making you feel as helpless as a two year old child.  The toddler can crawl faster than walk, he will fall over if he sprints for more than a short distance, his light source is a teddy-bear that lights up when hugged, water is a nono, everything seems much larger and daunting, he can't reach doorknobs without something to climb on, and his lack of fine motor skills makes the clunkyness of ""click and hold"" mouse interactions feel right.The foreshadowing is great.  A lot of the clues you get to the story are in the environment or depicted as a two-year-old's scribbled drawing.Though the  length is short but feels accurate for the game, it is hard to say that a 3-4 hour game with little to no replay value  should be $20.  The reason why I say that it has  no replay value is the fact that the game relies so heavily on the unknown and the imagination for the fear to work, that there will be nothing worth seeing again given that the gameplay is a little ""slow""If you really like horror games,  you probably already own this game, but if you don't, then you need to go get it.  It's worth the full price if you are a fan of the genre; otherwise, wait for a sale, but be sure to grab it when the price drops.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=528707572"
