,Recommended,250620,11567645,"Posted: 5 August, 2014",all,Nourishment M.O.T.,"Okay, okay. For all those kids out there that think it's one or two hours of gameplay, get real. Why do you even play games, if you are in such a rush to finish them? Think of this as a great film... I got four to five hours out of it. Yes, 20 is a bit much... but if I am lucky, the Dlc will be free. (Right.) Anyway, to those of you that think this is going to change the way you play. NOOOOOOO! The story is genius, to me at least. You won't understand how brilliant it is if you are just a kid. This is aimed at adults and if you have children or grew up in a bad home, it will make sense. To everybody else, you'll be wondering why you never get to kill anybody. Grow up, then come back to this.This game really is brilliant and should be played by anybody who has children. It is not perfect, not even close, but it does tell a very important story that is sad, scary and beautiful. I know not a lot of people are willing to admit when a game spooks them or makes them feel uneasy, yet I will tell you this, I was spooked out by a part in this more than any other game I have ever played.Now, this is best played with headphones on in the dark. A lot of reviews spoiled some of the most intense moments, so dont read too much into the story. The graphics are nothing special, but they do the job and the enviroments are nice to look at. I also found the creature to be well designed.The puzzles are far too easy and end up being things that just slow you down more than test your wits. Still, the story and atmosphere are amazing. The real let down is the price since this game is very short and doesn't bring anything new to the table. If you catch it on offer, it is a must own."
,Recommended,250620,10363679,"Posted: 5 June, 2014",all,s▼ni†y burgl∆r,"Wow, this game was pretty amazing. One of the main reasons I got it was because of the fact that you played as a toddler, which was something I've never seen before in a game. And the other, well, because I'm an indie/horror enthusiast, so this looked really promising.The atmoshpere and level design are extremely creepy and dark, almost Tim Burton-esque. Every level was heavily detailed and as such helped me feel very immersed. What I like about it is that it is subtle, like Amnesia - nothing is really too forceful with trying to shove terror down your throat, instead it just eases it down nice and slowly, making sure you suffer every last bit. I really underestimated the game's horror factor, because it has moments where it's right up there with Outlast in making me bleed out sweat.The gameplay is pretty good; it captures the movements of a toddler very well. Walking upright, you waddle around like you're drunk, and you can also crawl on the floor, which is actually a lot faster. You can run while you are upright, but you risk the chance of tumbling down to the ground, so I never really did that. One thing I really found annoying was the teddy bear as your light source, because he obstructed a lot of my view towards the ground, which made it very difficult at times to be able to see objects, or where I was heading. Not to mention, he does not provide a very good radius of light, although perhaps maybe that is a problem with how I set my gamma, not sure.Well anyway, yeah, epic game, but the only problem is, it was too short! :C But oh well. I still do strongly recommend you get this if you want horror similar to Amnesia and with a bit of a psychological feel to it."
