76561198165112475,Recommended,250620,21034011,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,darkstarr5,"I would like to start off by saying that I rarely play horror games.  Among the Sleep caught my attention by its promise of an emersive I rarely play horror games as I am a little bit of a wimp when it comes to being scared.  However, Among the Sleep caught my attention with its promise of an immersive world and a new perspective.  Both of which it delivered very well.  I started the game expecting to be scared out of my mind, but this game was very mild on the horror spectrum.  There was a small hand full of times that my heart raced and I jumped a little.  Very reminiscent of my childhood days when I remember being afraid to walk around the house in the dark because my imagination had already created all of the worst possible things that could be waiting to grab me.The biggest complaint I read in reviews was that the game was too short.  And really it was, however I also don’t think it should have been much longer.  The puzzles were relatively simple.  I got lost a couple of times in areas that seemed a little circular and the right direction was hard to decipher.  Otherwise the game moved at a steady pace.I’m glad I played this game and would recommend it to anyone looking for something to occupy a few hours of their time.  Seeing the world from the height of a 2 year old gave a fresh perspective and I believe the development and design of the game was very well done."
