,Recommended,250620,26355223,"Posted: 1 November, 2016",all,Evaheist,"It's a nice short and atmospheric game. Not worth 30 quid but if you're a horror fan, you can't go wrong with it when it's on sale.The environments are creepy and the sound design is top-notch (although I can't figure out why the baby himself/herself sound like a monster themselves sometimes). There's isn't much in the way of puzzle solving or anything besides moving objects and pushing stuff around.Graphics look gorgeous. The lighting is superb.Be wary, though. There are clipping bugs galore; so don't be surprised if you get stuck on the environment occasionally and can't move. I had to restart a couple of levels because I got stuck in the ground and wound up where the game apparently didn't want me to be. Gameplay mechanics are pretty easy and I'm sure your non-gamer significant other can enjoy it as much as you do. Can't say it had much in the way of surprises or the story was that special but it did keep me interested throughout the 3-or-so hour experience. Sometimes I felt the developers had the atmosphere and story down but couldn't really come up with any new ideas for gameplay.As I said earlier, if you find this on sale and you're into horror and toddling simulation, you'll get your bang out of Among the Sleep."
