76561198042480550,Recommended,250620,10316232,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,Wolf,"WOW! A pretty scary game! Thank you Krillbite Studios for making this game, I had been waiting to play this for ages. I would recommend this game happily for any horror game lovers!"
76561198017704117,Recommended,250620,10325337,"Posted: 2 June, 2014",all,NinjaShade,"Despite (literally) crawling through this game, stopping to admire the art direction, slowing down to analyze the rather ingenious creative decisions by the Krillbite team, and simply standing frozen in terror on one end of a hallway, I blazed through this whole game in less than 4 hours, and it seems that the length is something that people have been rather disappointed about.Well, I'm going to share my opinion with you, and go on record to say that the length of this game... is... PERFECT. Krillbite doesn't beat around the bush, trying to draw out the gameplay with collectibles, and almost unattainable achievements, or the like. Instead, It focuses on its story, and sticks to it, allowing the player to truly immerse themselves in the unique scenario. There are sometimes lulls in the feeling of insecurity that you'll get while playing, but even in the calmer moments (with perhaps the exception of the VERY start of the game) there is never a moment failing to build tension.As a horror game alone, this title is very good, but it seemed like much more than that. The main draw of ""Among the Sleep"" is, of course, your character; that of a two year old child. Fear for a two year old and fear for an adult are two completely separate things, so when I say this game is more than just a game, I view it as an incredibly realistic look in to the child psyche. As I played through, I would have very vivid moments recollecting childhood fears. Things that are now commonplace were once terrifying! In a way, ""Among the Sleep"" brought back very VERY distant memories for me that I hadn't touched in ages. In one particular example, I had to put down my controller for a minute and just stare at the screen. Somehow, the creators had managed to build the scene before me as an almost perfect mimic of a recurring nightmare I would have as a small child. I'm not ashamed to say I stared at it for minutes before being able to proceed! In fact, the only thing I feel after beating this game is impressed.This game is surely going to be more personal for some than others, but it is a must have for lovers of the horror genre, and an interesting experiment even for those who don't normally find a good time in such things. Some people will say that the $20 price tag is too steep, but hey... support the independence! Right? Do that and Krillbite will surely be able to make more amazing titles for us in the future!""Among the Sleep""'s story is one that will draw you in and make you want to finish, and therein lies its greatest strength."
