76561197976028334,Recommended,250620,13616182,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,Get Burned!,"I really liked Among the Sleep. They did a good job with putting the player in the role of a 2 year old and seeing the world through his eyes. The game isn't really scary. It does have tense moments, though. It's dark, disorienting and sometimes confusing...like how the world can seem to little kids at night. This is a fantasy game set in the world of the kids projections of his surroundings as he tries to find his mom. There was one part in the beginning that really creeped me out. The kid is seemingly all alone in his room, but a man's voice is clearly heard giggling from somewhere nearby, unseen, like a psycho murderous clown waiting to leap out and murder the kid. I'll say no more about that! The puzzles of the game were really easy to figure out, but this was a really fun and interesting world to explore. The art direction is fantastic. The atmosphere of the game is really well done. The game is only a few hours long. I'm a busy guy and I appreciate that I was able to start and finish it in one night. The only part that actually seemed like padding is the added DLC that is essentially a side story that was only slightly related to the main game. Still, it was nice to have that extra little bit to play when the game was done. I suggest playing this one in the dark with head phones, and turning the brightness down. Among the Sleep is solid and an easy recommendation."
