76561197965282243,Recommended,250620,10962474,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Hatch,"If you're a fan of horror games this is worth playing.  You play as a 2 yr old and venture through a dream world, or should I say nightmare world.  The game starts out a little slow and seems more like a ""baby simulator"" but shortly after things pick up it gets creepy!  This horror adventure game does have its scares and environmental chill but it's not the scariest game out there.  In my opinion it's perfect for those who are trying to ease into the horror genre or just don't want anything too extreme.  But this game shouldn't be dismissed.  Like the other best horror games you can't fight the thing chasing you, all you can do is run and hide.  With a first person view and dark environments Among the Sleep gives you a feeling of being a child all alone.  There are items to find on you're way and places to hide.  If you want a creepy adventure this game is a must.Pros:+Graphics (not the best but still very good)+First-person view+Scares and environment+Not boringCons:-Sometimes climbing is finicky-The game is a bit short-The ending was anticlimactic"
