76561198108827327,Recommended,250620,10311319,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,drillpogodrill,"The only thing keeping this game from a perfect score is the length... it IS a short game with nothing to invite the player to try again. No diverging paths, or unlockable items. But it is exactly the way that ATS gets away from video game conventions that makes you love it. You wouldn't think a game with no violence and a toddler for a protagonist could scare you, but I found myself sitting on the cliche edge-of-my-seat both playing and watching.Pricey for the limited run length, but well worth the money for me. My roommates and I had a blast, laughing at each other and screaming at turns, and I have paid many times this price for games that didn't manage to do HALF that.  A solid 8 out of 10 that could've been a ten at about twice the length. Worth a run through, and making me eager to see what else the creators come up with."
76561197994954270,Recommended,250620,10311398,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,DeltaExTwo,"Among the Sleep is a good game in it's genre, but a few shortcomings keep it from being one of the best. But let's get the good things out of the way first. First off, the game has spectacular sound design. There's always something going on in the world and you're kept on your toes at all times. Secondly, Krillbite really nailed the perspective of a child, gameplay wise and design wise. You feel helpless and you really feel like a child in the sick twisted places that the game has to offer. Also the controls are fluid and simple, the way it should be. The negatives are that the puzzles aren't really anything to write home about, with simplistic 'find item and use item' puzzles, that could've been shaken up a bit to make them more interesting and diverse. Another thing is that the game is rather short, with an average playthrough probably taking about 2-2,5 hours to complete. It really leaves you wanting more and with a premise like this, you would've expected a little more from it. Not to mention the ending, which felt rushed and was ultimately very disappointing. The price is a bit hefty for such a short game, so it's up to you to decide whether or not this game is worth your time and investment. It was worth mine, but check out the demo if you feel uncertain."
