76561198060644485,Not Recommended,250620,26309579,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,rcrocker,"I was pretty neutral but on the negative side of this game. First I didnt really find it scary at all, and I've always found myself to pretty susceptible to tht sort of thing. It really felt like the developers wanted you to play this game in VR cuz that deffinately would have added to it. Next the visuals were pretty shotty. I dont have the best computer, but things were clipping in and out of each other all the time. This made the game hard to get into. On the brighter side the atmosphere is great. The story is good too. Dispite issuses I had with the gameplay I found myself drawn to finish the story. Unlike a lot of other horror games where you have to go around and read everything in order to get the plot, this game doesnt do that. It does a good job with visual clues to help you figure everything out; building to the final reveal. The last negative would be the play time. I finished the game in just under four hours which was a little shorter than it should have been. There are a few collectables hidden thoughout the game to go back and look for, but seeing as how they arnt anything but incohesive crayon drawings there is no real reason.Conclusion: at five bucks on sale it is hard to say no, but unless you can get this thing to work with a VR headset I say you might want to look around a bit more first"
