,Recommended,250620,12117710,"Posted: 16 September, 2014",all,Elensar,"So I finished the game and I have to say, although it wasn't as scary as I was expecting, it was creepy enough to give me a few chills.  I loved seeing the world through a childs eyes and the little details were really cool, like the ""spooky world"" was just the baby's imagination interacting with the house, the key on the baby stairs gate for example, everything was significant to building up a story of this child, the drawings of sad child and grumpy monster etc.I loved the level with the bottles all over the place that could fall and break, you really got a feeling of panic that how angry mummy would be if you made even the slightest noise etc, at least that's the impression I got.It was also really refreshing to have this sad situation where for once it isn't the stereotype drunken father routine, I really liked that.One thing though I would liked to have seen better use off was Teddy.  Although he serves as a kind of ""flash light"" mechanic, you can literally play through the entire game having never used him if you want to.  It would have been really cool if there was some sort of ""upset"" meter or something that would have you needing to cuddle him to stop the baby from crying or something and attracting the ""monster""  it would also have been good that if after an encounter when the screen goes all crazy because you're scared that you need to cuddle teddy to reset that.  Basically I just felt that teddy wasn't used enough which is a shame.The game should have been longer for the price asked... I paid £8.99 and that was with a 40% discount, and while I don't feel that I have been ripped off, I certainly wish the game was a good bit longer... I kind of feel that we were only really starting to encounter threats when the game started to come to an end.Would very much like to see more of this, hopefully some additional content will come from dlc or a sequel, but either way I would recommend to give this a try.  It's a fresh take on the horror fps genre and it's cute scary and funI'd give Among the sleep 7/10 lossing a little score for its price to duration ratio."
