,Recommended,250620,11209635,"Posted: 12 July, 2014",all,Blood_Skull_Boi84,"Among The Sleep is an atmospheric, puzzling game that plays like a horror game but is technically an atmosphere test in disguise. Finally a studio that creates horror that decided to take a frickin' break from all the blood, gore and overexcessive monster designs. Now we have a monster that is completely black, hides in shadows, and each form of it rumored to be the child's parents. I'd favor to talk about each aspect of the game and what it does well.THE STORY: 60% 6/10To be honest I didn't like the story, because it didn't make any sense. Also it was too abbrieviated and ended way too fast. It would be nice to have a couple more levels according to the little video at the end of the ATS demo. Those in my opinion looked way nicer and refined. Also if you were to add the missing levels as DLC I would screech, that would be nice. So basically the story is you are a two year old child who goes to sleep one night only to be awoken by some noises and a supposed paranormal being. It is only until you  find out your mother is missing  and see the first monster you know things are wrong. You take your teddy bear and venture through three stages *Five technically throughout the entire game*. It's... a nice concept but as I said. It doesn't make sense and it's too brief. At least explain in the game how this happened!THE LEVEL DESIGN: 100% (Solid 10/10)The level design is ABSOLUTELY GORGEOUS! I seriously love every single part of it and it's entirety. It kept my one, colorful eye on the screen and it's like a replacement for the story. The story is low brow but the graphics are the highlight of this game. Every single level is amazing and beautiful. It's odd how something so spooky can be such eye candy at the same time. The level design even reminded me of myself since when I was younger I had odd, strange dreams from time to time that resembled this game, and after I saw Among The Sleep's level design I flipped my♥♥♥♥♥♥and went totally crazy over this game. I'm even working on a game similiar to this that will be created on Unity, *Fun fact, Among The Sleep was also made on Unity*THE CHARACTERS 90% (9/10)Now there aren't many characters in Among The Sleep. *If you don't count the monsters, I'm not counting them since they've got no personalities and just want to capture you*, pretty much we have the child themself, the child's mother, Teddy, and the supposed father of the child which we can get traces of in the introduction of the mother in the first chapter. I'll talk about the mother first. The mother is the supposed main antagonist (due to her connection with the odd tree monster in the fourth act) By the end she seems to be a redeemed villain and still loves the main protagonist. Now we should talk about Teddy. He is one of the main protagonist alongside the child and he helps them manuever through the nightmarish parts of his dreams. The ending which involved Teddy is very creative and I love his character.CONCLUSION:Among The Sleep is a great horror game to play at night due to the buildup and spook the game brings. I recommend this game, it gets a 9/10!Have a nice day."
