,Not Recommended,250620,31545855,Posted: 4 May,all,Dakusan,"So far I am really not a fan of this game at all.It is often too dark and I can't see anything, even with brightness way up. I got stuck near the beginningWhere I was supposed to extract the teddy from the washerfor like 15 minutes as I somehow missed the icon that said I could open it, and everything else was so dark I thought I had been missing something elsewhere. It is obviously trying to do the ""follow the light"" thing, which is ""proper game design"", but they don't do it very well. In the ""first level"", I had a lot of trouble finding one of the specific [same] items I needed to continue as it was down a ""path"" that just looked like most of the rest of the empty wooded area.The novelty of playing as a baby is, while a neat idea, ultimately just another gimmick. It did not add to the atmosphere or ""fear"" factor at all for me. If they had made a rift version, I might have changed my mind on that, but as they said, it doesn't fit the game movement style.Ultimately, it's really just a walking simulator with a few intractable objects. No puzzles, or mini games, or even scavenger hunts (which makes something like Gone Home stand out). No thought. Just ""look for something that might be a path and see if it has a thing you need"". I really felt (and would bet some money) that this was made by game dev students at a college, in which they were told ""this is the right way to do a game"", and they just tried to follow the standard formulas.I'll update this when I finish the game (doing a run for achievements so it doesn't negatively add to my game completion rate) but I don't expect it to get any better."
