,Recommended,250620,10403889,"Posted: 9 June, 2014",all,UnbridledEnd,"Great, terrifying game. From a design perspective, choosing to make the main character a baby is brilliant. It's like the hopless feeling you get when playing Amnesia, but dramatically increased. Speaking of Amnesia, the gameplay will be very familiar to veterans. Walk around (sometimes crawl), move things, pick things up. Pieces of the story are subtly told through childish drawings found in various locations. It's enough to be able to accurately predict what's really going on, yet it isn't stated plainly, giving you a sense of accomplishment.The jump scares were usually done on my own accord, like making the baby breathe harder after running, or knocking something over. The ambience, as well as the creeping fear that something unstoppable is following you, sets the stage for you to scare yourself. And then, when you laugh at yourself, something intentionally terrifying happens, and you go change your underwear.For those that care, the graphics are decent. Average to low poly models, relatively low resolution textures, but they get the job done. They are readable enough that you can tell a key from a doorknob, which is all it really needs. You won't have much time to focus on the scenery, or if you do, adjusting your view will make you realize that something was focusing back at you."
,Recommended,250620,10408005,"Posted: 9 June, 2014",all,PistolOverYou3500,This is the best horror game i have ever played. If your looking for a short thrilling horrow game this is it.
