,Not Recommended,250620,10374496,"Posted: 6 June, 2014",all,BrandonBloX,"This one is a little difficult for me to go with a YES or NO. Some points I want to make.I've been seeing this compared to Outlast & Amnesia. Cut it out. The similarities end with it being ""horror"" genre, and the only option you have when facing trouble is run or hide.Positives ++Eerie scenery. (what kinda got me to check it out,it looked at first that it would have an American McGee's Wonderland feel)+Loved the visuals+Cool soundtrack.+Plenty noises and things that would terrify a toddler, amped up to make it spooky.+Pretty imaginative. Remember back on  the things that scared you as a child... well, yea, a lot of that.Negatives --Far too short. I even spent some time exploring the levels. Soaking in the scenery. Managed to finish around 2 hours.-Took awhile for me to learn any repercussions in the game. The Teddy would suggest being quiet, and I just would go about my business. Even chased a monster down in the woods before it disappeared trying to see if anything would happen. Wasn't until it caught me later near the end of the game, that I learned the monster does infact interact with you.-Very simplistic puzzles. (which I get it, you're a baby.)- How you're expecting the story to end, it pretty much does.-Just wasn't really ever that scared. I think knowing that I was a child, and that harm to a child in any game is pretty much taboo... I felt basically invincible the entire time. (at one point in time, to sate my curiosity, I did drown myself. lol. but just the thought that no real danger would come to me, created a ""Star power"" mentality.)Side notes-Lots of foreshadowing. Pay attention to things said earlier on, drawings on paper and chalked on the walls. You'll know where the story is heading.If you ever saw the 1995 movie, Tales from the Hood, the similarity between the two makes it very hard to not see the metaphor the game implies.But, it was very cool for an indie game. However in my opinion, 19.99 is sorta steep for what is offered with this game. If you can get it on sale, do it.I am looking forward to see what the developers come up with the future."
