,Recommended,250620,12079158,"Posted: 12 September, 2014",all,The D,"At first glance, the game seems a little pricey for the hours logged. But, one thing that is worth noting is that the game has very little down time. The pacing is good and the game alterantes primarily between suspence and intensity. Had it been longer, it would have worn out its charm. And had it been less expensive... Well, everyone has to make a living, and I'm sure a lot of work went the game. It's very polished and the visuals and sound are fantastic, so I don't feel ripped off.The two hours (ish... I left it paused for a little while) I got from the game were as fulfilling as any ""full length"" game, just condensed.I think a lot of people expect more out of games in terms of value, but that doesn't always seem fair. Considering how much you end up paying to see a movie at the theater, or for a a few rounds of drinks at a bar, this game starts to look like a pretty good deal. Overall, no matter how much you think you're getting ripped off, chances are good that a video game is still the best value in terms of hours per dollars spent."
