,Not Recommended,250620,10333022,"Posted: 3 June, 2014",all,KyuKyu-chan,"Among the Sleep. A horror from 2 years old perspective. Sounds rather interesting, don't you agree? I was waiting for the game since the start of the Kickstarter campaign. And to my embitterment, the game has disappointed me.First of all - this game is supposed to be a horror. While the game has that uncomfortable atmosphere, it failed to scare me even once (and I'm rather easy to scare off). Sudden loud noises (and many sounds like rustle, sound of something being scraped etc.)   lightning pop-ups, ""monsters"", which look like they were taken from a kid's cartoon - they are not scary for a grown-up. I would understand if the game was positioned as horror for kids, but it wasn't.Second - graphics. The design of the game is well made. Everything looks good  and not out of order, like a child would've seen (big scary coats in the dark closet, big furniture and other stuff like that). The only con is glitchy textures - they tended to disappear on my PC.Audio. Except sudden loud noises, music is very well made. It's very atmospheric and goes well with the game.Gameplay. The game is very straight - the objective of the game is to collect ""memories"" and find your mom. While doing so, you will face various obstacles (from closed doors, on which you can not reach the door knob and need to place a chair and got on it first to closed doors where you would need a key). When you need to reach high places, you will need to climb on them  using drawers, chairs and other thing. It's fun, but repetitive. The great thing is the message that the story holds (review  is spoiler free, so I'll just note that).One thing has bothered me - why a two year old child can push very heavy objects, throwing some of them  at a distance of two meters, climbing without taking a break like a professional athlete? Big chairs, tires - two year old doesn't have that amount strength.The game was promised to last for at least 3 hours, but I finished it in 90 minutes. It's really short for the money it costs. 20€ (18 with discount) is TOO much. You can buy it for 5, but not 20 Euro.So, in the end:Pros:+ Music+ Atmosphere-+ Graphics (+- because of glitchy textures)+ StoryCons:- The non-existent horror part- Repetitive gameplay- Baby has super strength- Very short- OverpricedConclusion: If you want to play this game, wait for big sale or you'll just overpay like I did. 5/10"
