76561198040187605,Recommended,250620,19219383,"Posted: 22 November, 2015",all,Chibiusa,"I just finished my first play through. It took a couple of months to finish because I played a few minutes at a time, but it took me about an hour to finish the game.I loved the experience. I'm a mom of a 2-year-old, which is why I bought the game in the first place. The story is heartbreaking and most of what's creepy about this comes from the fact that this is a neglected child. Can't get much worse than that :(That said, I'm not an expert on child psychology, but it's funny, and I say this as a mom, how accurate the game is when it comes to being a toddler. They do climb on chairs and drawers and do dangerous things without considering what could go wrong. The mechanics are totally plausible.It's very clear that the world and the events are how a very young, abused child sees them: distorted. This is also why the game is so scary, you kinda go through the house looking for your mommy but at the same time know that if you make a mistake (e.g. break a bottle), you'll regret it. Fear of someone you love is just terrible, especially if you're so vulnerable, and this game does a great job of getting you in that state of mind.This game has a great story and it makes you think about childhood, especially as a parent!"
