,Recommended,250620,13914451,"Posted: 9 January, 2015",all,Cynical Pancake,"I was recommended this game a short while ago and decided that I would give it a try.I picked this up at the full price, so one thing I will say is that while I thoroughly enjoyed my experience playing this, I don't feel as though it is worth the fairly hefty pricetag for a short indie game.One of the first things that I enjoyed about this title was the voice acting - it fits in perfectly and really helps to set the characters. I was really impressed with the art style and the overall atmosphere of the game genuinely had me spooked at times without having to rely on the trope of jump scares aplenty.I will not include spoilers but the ending was just right. It was touching, a little surprising and rounded the game off very well. I just wish that it had come a little later as I expected to get more than 2 hours worth of gameplay for £14.99.I have recommended it to my friends, but I would say to wait for the sales. While I love supporting cretaive indie developers and unique and interesting new games, I don't feel that it was worth the full price but it is certainly a game I thoroughly enjoyed and will not soon forget."
