,Recommended,250620,14002970,"Posted: 15 January, 2015",all,RAIZO,"I like Among the Sleep, and though I wish I could say that I ‘love’ Among the Sleep, I just can’t; not with its overly simplified puzzles and super short length.  Literally, it will take only about an hour, and little more than that, to beat and there really isn’t anything to go back through for as far as gameplay/replay is concerned, but the developers just added a prologue chapter (to be played after the regular game is completed) as free DLC, so that kind of makes up for what the game is lacking in.Granted, this is a game wherein the protagonist is a 2 yr. old boy (so you wouldn't expect overly difficult puzzles) that stumble-walks/crawls his way through dark, mysterious environments with his talking/walking hug-it-to-light-your-way teddy bear, looking for objects to unlock memories related to what is ultimately going on - not gonna specify on that and spoil anything for anyone who hasn’t played this yet, so just play and find out for yourself (it will be worth it in the end as this is a psychological/pseudo-horror game and the revelation is truly heartbreaking --- this is something I felt the developers conveyed to the gamer wonderfully well).I definitely recommend this game when you can get it on sale for at least 50% off, and the graphics and especially the sound design are pretty good and work well with the game’s theme, but it mostly just feels like a ‘good start’ for the developers and there needs to be more of a game next time around.  I definitely look forward to seeing what they follow this up with and any mistakes made with this game should certainly prove helpful when creating a new one."
76561197977894271,Recommended,250620,14024629,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,aweir14150,"A psychological horror game of a different breed...If you were expecting a slash-and-hack type of survival game, you will be very disappointed.If, however, you were expecting a genuinely terrifying, psychologically horrifying, creepy, atmospheric  horror game, this is the game you have been waiting for.One factor which makes this game so unique as a horror game is the complete absence of any fighting. If anything, to survive, you must hide. But don't let that dissuade you. In fact it increases your ""flight"" response and makes it scarier.I literally had goosebumps and chills running up and down my spine for the better part of this game because it is truly that scary. The atmosphere and sound effects of this game is unmatched by any other horror game I have played. The only thing that ever came close to this was possibly the Silent Hill series; if you into that type of suspense and atmosphere, this game will deliver. However as far as gore is concerned, there is none. But who woulda thought that a game with no gore or blood and guts could be so scary?I rate this game an 8.5/10The only reason why I did not give it a higher rating is because as far as the game's story goes, I think the very ending could have been a little better.The graphics are good but not amazing, but the atmosphere (and especially the sound effects) are well done.Sound effects alone I would rate a 9/10Graphics would get am 8/10"
