,Recommended,250620,14372838,"Posted: 7 February, 2015",all,Mctwispx,"Among the Sleep is a different sort of horror game in that it utilizes jump scares, creepy ambiance, and heartpumping adrenaline spikes rather than outright gory, bloody, horror. It's whimsically odd in aspects that are reminiscent of Alice in Wonderland, and creepy in aspects that closely resemble that of Slender/Amnesia. It's fun to play, might even get you a few times with some scares, and is completely worth it.This game surprised me in more ways than I expected. I was consistently trying to figure out the plot and whenever I thought I had it, it would change on me. The bear for one is somewhat creepy on it's own, and when you first begin to meet and interact with Teddy it feels very reminsicent of Chucky. As the game plays forward however, Teddy is your best friend in the entire world, as you navigate through a world that feels like the ""Other Mother"" built it (Coraline reference!). There's simple puzzles to complete to progress as you go, but they aren't mind-numbingly simple, some of them take a few minutes to put together.The story itself gives a fresh new way of looking at this kind of situation through a child's perspective. You're playing as a two year old child, and your objective is to rescue your mother from this nightmarish, topsy-turvey, alternate version of your own world. The ambiance is amazing, and the graphics are impeccable. It can get truly terrifying.I bought this game on a daily deal for 66% off. Among the Sleep isn't a very long game, it's only roughly 3 hrs of playthrough, so I feel better about paying 6$ vs 20$ to be honest. It's gamepad compatable, and if you're using a pc with Windows it goes without saying that it's recommended you use an Xbox 360 controller.It's fun, short, but not so sweet! If you can swing it, pick up Among the Sleep and play it, it's worth it."
,Recommended,250620,14375737,"Posted: 7 February, 2015",all,Locksheon,"This is a beautiful game, with haunting visuals and implications.   Don't forget to go to ""Chapter Select"" and play the prologue when you're done!The game is rather short (which isn't bad for this genre).  The entire playthrough might take you 2-3 hours, but you will be intrigued, scared, and thrilled almost the entire time.  It's definately worth playing, but paying full price might be too much for some folks.  I got my copy on sale for 7 dollars, and I was NOT disappointed!"
