,Recommended,250620,14442993,"Posted: 12 February, 2015",all,Xayaa,"Sooooo.... I, personally, hate kids.They're just pooping, crying sacks of meat for the first few years of their lives, and then after that they grow into spoiled brats, obnoxious teens, and potentially crazy adults...HOWEVER, that's all beside the point as Among The Sleep, complete with ""goo goo ga ga"" baby sounds as ambiance, is a very good game. I picked it up while it was on sale and I certainly don't regret it. Sometimes there are glitches in lighting and movement is stiff, but the tale it tells is enthralling and dark. Without spoiling it for you, I highly suggest you look up no plot/storyline before playing the game -- I didn't and it opened up about 50 unforeseen storylines all made up in my head. Any time I was wandering around unsure of where to go, my mind was stewing up this beautiful schmorgesborg of storylines, making literally every second entertaining.I've tried Slenderman games and a few other ""atmospheric horror"" games, but Among The Sleep is the only one I've been able to get through 100%. Complete with frequent ""AH OH **** OH MY GOD GET AWAY FROM ME OH ****,"" there are plenty of instances of jump scares while not  being overwhelming -- the anxiety inducing wait is far worse than the scare, of course, but isn't that why you're looking at this game anyway?The really scary part, however, is, even though you're PLAYING a two year old, you tend to feel more like you're PROTECTING a two year old -- this is a clever tactic that I've yet to see in any other game (mostly because I've never played a game from the perspective of an infant). Though the game runs extremely short, comparatively speaking, I really support the length the developers took it to -- it's certainly not too long, and they keep their story ""short and sweet,"" so to speak. They get across everything they need to in just a few hours of gaming.So if a short but very good atmospheric horror game is something you're interested in playing, pick this title up. You won't regret it.Oh yeah. Also, you get to brag about being a two year old... Do people brag about that?.."
