,Recommended,250620,10945727,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,ZoeyTheSnek,"Among the Sleep is not your typical horror game. It is a bit short, but not as short as the 1 hour playtime that I've seen others give. I'd say it's a solid 2-3 hour game, a little more if you explore the environment (which you should). It's got a beautiful, touching story that reveals itself gradually. The environments you travel through are varied and very rich, with minimal texture reusing, which is unusual and refreshing in an indie game. The atmosphere is perfect and creepy, but not chock full of jump scares. The first parts of the game will lull you into a false sense of security. To say anything more would be a spoiler.There's no incentive to replay unless you missed a Steam achievement, and this game isn't really made for replays because the story will have been revealed. However, I think the first experience was solid enough and unique enough to stand on its own. I got it for $15.99 and thought it was well worth the price because it seems much higher quality than other indie games and I am very interested to see what else the developers can do. I highly recommend it!"
