76561198054867309,Recommended,250620,12872876,"Posted: 10 November, 2014",all,But'th Why'th,"Before I begin, this game is very good. So when i first heard of Among the Sleep and started looking into it, it looked like a cool game with a good concept, one where you play as a child. This idea is brilliantly shown in the actual game with everything being bigger or twisted in some way due to children seeing things differently to adults. In terms of the gameplay, this game is clever. You can alternate between standing and crawling as well as using items such as chairs to reach higher places i.e. a door handle. In terms of what the game does best it is its approach to horror and tension. It doesnt throw out a lot of jump scares with it building up tension using sights and sounds for instance a passing glimpse of some other creature or hearing a door slam. It is nearer the end of the game in which you start to encounter some other creaturs but I am not saying how this is done.Overall this game is clever and very good even though it is only 2-3 hours long. Also the recently released free downloadable content adds a strong 20 minutes of additional gameplay, one which is a prologue to the events of the main game. I would thorougly recommend this game to anyone."
,Recommended,250620,13063994,"Posted: 23 November, 2014",all,Mortaire,"I've always been a fan of indie games, particularly indie horror games. I went into Among the Sleep with minimal information, I just saw that you played as a infant, and I knew I had to have it. The adventure that followed starting from 12 to around 3 in the morning some might say was shortlived, however I loved every bit of it. The atmosphere, symbolism, and thought that this game provokes stemming from the question of what is real and what is imagination from the point of a two year old was comparable in complexity to the ending of Bioshock Infinite. I also find it comparable to movies such as American Psycho and Donnie Darko in the same way. Not everyone will have the same interpretation, although I have heard very good ones in the forums. If you expect from this game cheap jumps scares or award winning graphics or action, look somewhere else. This game is more of an allegory within a haunting art form, and I will fondly remember those nearly three hours I spent on this game, as  I will also remember what I took away."
