76561198031383772,Recommended,250620,13023321,"Posted: 20 November, 2014",all,Revanaught,"I really wish their was a neutral options, because I don't nessicarily recomend or not recommend this game.  It's okay.  It's certainly not a horror game and the ""twists"" are painfull obvious.  The atmosphere is really nice and I really like the concept, but it feels like the game is trying to be scary without anything that's actually scary.  You don't encounter an enemy until you're 3/4 through the game, and if an enemy catches you it merely resets you about 10 feet back from where you were caught and now the enemy no longer spawns, meaning there's no punishment for being caught and therefore no tension.  There are also quite a few issues with textures clipping through each other, partciuarly with your characters hands when climbing.  The graphics aren't spectacular.  Opening drawers shows a clearly flat texture, with no attempt to make anything inside the drawer look remotely 3D.  It's also incredibly short, no more than an hour and a half long.  It has charm, it's atmospheric but it falls flat in a number of areas.  Only get it if it's on sale."
