76561197971739421,Recommended,250620,29590299,Posted: 30 January,all,Zergling Rush Of Adorableness!,"Rarely will I come across a game that throws you into such a dramatically different perspective. Among The Sleep is a refreshing change to the usual games we all have. Not only does this one throw you into the world of a 2 year old, it shows you just how a child may view the world and the life around him in a very unique way.This game plays it's horror cards perfectly as it slowly reveals the child's life in a very dark and disturbing way. You start off in a world full of colour and brightness - how a child's view should be - but this quickly changes to the darkness that a child should never have to experience.There are simple challenges that compliment how a child may solve it and this in no way makes the game silly or frustrating. Everything works in perfect unison. Even the environment itself as you navigate really makes you feel so small in the big wide world you woddle around in. Speaking of woddling, the developers really captured the movements/sounds/actions of a 2 year old child.Unfortunately there are some issues in this game. You may find a few bugs and glitches as you progress, even to the point where you get stuck and cannot move. I was able to wiggle myself out of any areas I got glitched/stuck into. Be aware the saving function in the game does NOT save your location, only what you've collected and the chapter you're up to. If you exit out of the game you will start back at the beginning of the chapter.Nearing the end of this game I really craved familiarity and pretty colours and brightness. Having delved into this poor child's dark life for so long I couldn't wait to get out of it and see what I saw at the beginning. Overall a brilliant game in its portrayal, message, story and feeling. It is a short game but honestly take your time and really explore and enjoy."
