,Recommended,250620,31307965,Posted: 22 April,all,oliverklee,"This is a first-person survival horror game from the perspective of a two-year old toddler. It's quite short (2.5-5 hours) and relatively easy.If you liked Ammesia: The Dark Descent, you will like this disturbing game.It provides a very intense, dark atmosphere with relative simple, but nice graphics and great music. Playing as a 2-year old brings a unique touch to the game both in the way you move as well as how you can interact with the environment.The only downsides are the clunky controls and some glitches in the graphics, the physics and the sound. In addition, the save points are too far away (while the respawn points are okay). So dying is not a problem, but if you plan to play this game in more than one session, I recommend stopping a session right after you've reached a new chapter.Play this game for experiencing the atmosphere. Don't play it as a challenge or to beat it."
