76561198098041932,Recommended,250620,34028864,Posted: 4 August,all,shugenjajvfx,"Wow. This game is something. Often, horror games rely on cheap tricks to scare you. Among the Sleep is no different but they are justified by its unique premise: You play a two year old toddler... and everything and everybody is terrifying to a baby. The game does a good job of simulating that feeling of helplessness and fear of what you cannot understand that I'm sure every kid that age feels. The ending was also heavy. Not to spoil anything, but your heart will sink when you realize what every scary, incomprehensible thing the child was imagining represented in real life. Two immersive thumbs up."
